       #  Answer:-
               -> Approach: The background-color property of CSS is used to set the background of an element. We can set 
              background color by selecting the element by its class name of id name and then apply the background-color 
              property on it to set the background color.
   
               -> To add background color in HTML, use the CSS background-color property. Set it to the color name or code
              you want and place it inside a style attribute. Then add this style attribute to an HTML element, like a 
              table, heading, div.

